                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            
                            <p>Letter from High Sheriff of County Galway, James R. Martin, to Sir Robert Chalmers (1858–1938), the under-secretary of Ireland. Martin writes about the Rising in county Galway, claiming that the requests for compensation are false claims. He reports that Sinn Fein sympathisers willingly assisted the rebels and are now seeking to be refunded by the crown.</p>
                            
                        
                            
                        
                            
                            <p>The high sheriff of County Galway was the sovereign's judicial representative in County Galway. Sir Robert Chalmers was sent to Ireland as replacement under-secretary for Sir Matthew Nathan, who had resigned along with Augustine Birrell, his chief secretary, following the outbreak of the Easter Rising in 1916.</p>
                            
                        
                    
                </note>
